<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Gartha</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-02 07:55:35</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Maybe you can't dual wield this, but paired with the Blade of Abrogation in your off hand, you will lay a severe hurting on something.  I have found that if you use a slower weapon in your off hand, but a very fast weapon in your primary, you attack almost as quickly as if you had 2 very fast weapons.  My warrior dual wielded langseaxes, and the second lang swung every other time my first one did.  When I switched to a well-balanced bastard sword, the same thing happened.  By the time the second attack came around for my first weapon, the delay for the slower secondary weapon had elapsed, making it eligible for the attack that a faster weapon would have gotten.  Of course, this was at level 18, so my dual wield was only 95.  Maybe when you're in your 30's and 40's your off hand procs more often, in which case my ENTIRE point is moot.  But should you manage, somehow, to get these two blades at like, level 15 or so ::coughcoughtwinktwink::  then above statements apply.</font></td></tr></table>
